<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#70)]" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d710a-70">
                            <head><hi rend="smallcaps">Editor’s Note</hi></head>
                            <p>—At an informal meeting of the Foreign Ministers held at 4 p.m. on
                                July 23, <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> stated that
                                he had expressed the views of the United States on the subject of
                                reparations from Germany to <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> at their meeting on the morning of July 23
                                and that he had subsequently informed <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> of this talk (see <ref target="#pg_295"><hi rend="italic">post</hi>, page 295</ref>). No other record of
                                this <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> conversation has been
                                found.</p>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>